  "sn36.2:1.1": "Linked Discourses 36 ",
  "sn36.2:2.1": "1 With Verses ",
  "sn36.2:3.1": "2 Pleasure",
  "sn36.2:4.1": "“Mendicants, there are these three feelings.",
  "sn36.2:4.2": "What three?",
  "sn36.2:4.3": "Pleasant, painful, and neutral feeling.",
  "sn36.2:4.4": "These are the three feelings.” ",
  "sn36.2:5.1": "“Whatever is felt",
  "sn36.2:5.2": "internally and externally—",
  "sn36.2:5.3": "whether pleasure or pain",
  "sn36.2:5.4": "as well as what’s neutral—",
  "sn36.2:6.1": "having known this as suffering,",
  "sn36.2:6.2": "delusive, falling apart,",
  "sn36.2:6.3": "one sees them vanish as they’re experienced again and again:",
  "sn36.2:6.4": "that’s how to lose interest in them.”"
}